3.text: A tourist from Sweden wants to go to the National Museum.
3.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>A tourist from Sweden wants to go to the National Museum.</prosody></speak>

4.text: Tourist : Excuse me. Where is the National Museum?
4.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Tourist : Excuse me. Where is the National Museum?</prosody></speak>

5.text: Sandaru : It's in the Main Street.
5.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'><phoneme alphabet='ipa' ph='sand̪əni'>Sandaru</phoneme> : It's in the Main Street.</prosody></speak>

6.text: Tourist : How can I go to the Main Street?
6.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'>Tourist : How can I go to the Main Street?</prosody></speak>

7.text: Sandaru : Go along this road and turn left. It's the Main Street.
7.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'><phoneme alphabet='ipa' ph='sand̪əni'>Sandaru</phoneme> : Go along this road and turn left. It's the Main Street.</prosody></speak>

9.text: Sandaru : There is a park on your right. Next to the park is the Museum. It is between the park and the Art Gallery. You can find it easily.
9.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'><phoneme alphabet='ipa' ph='sand̪əni'>Sandaru</phoneme> : There is a park on your right. Next to the park is the Museum. It is between the park and the Art Gallery. You can find it easily.</prosody></speak>

11.ssml: <speak><prosody rate='slow'><phoneme alphabet='ipa' ph='sand̪əni'>Sandaru</phoneme> :You're welcome. Enjoy your visit!</prosody></speak>
